pull_request.title: Update XKCP and avoid assembler .ifdef directives
pull_request.body: This is an attempt to fix Issue #1166. I don't have a machine to reproduce the issue on, so I'll need someone else to test the fix. The first pair of commits updates XKCP to the latest version. This alone won't fix the issue. The second pair of commits switches some `.ifdef` and `.ifndef` assembler directives to C preprocessor `#ifdef` and `#ifndef`, so we don't have to pass the `defsym` arguments which seem to be the problem in #1166.

pull_request.title: Bump oqs-sys/liboqs from `a39d08e` to `4d938b1`
pull_request.body:
Bumps [oqs-sys/liboqs](https://github.com/Open-Quantum-Safe/liboqs) from `a39d08e` to `4d938b1`.
Commits
  • 4d938b1 Update XKCP and avoid assembler .ifdef directives (#1173)
  • fde936b extend weekly run timeout [skip ci] (#1172)
  • a38d3ff adding constant time test as weekly github action (#1170)
  • 5608b46 remove picnic from cygwin build (#1171)
